For example, only 16 out of 34 States have adopted laws requiring the presentation of a photo ID card.
Nevertheless, the new rules put in place will undoubtedly make the exercise of the voting right more difficult in 2012.
Democrat critics denounce the partisan nature of the laws that have been voted on and see a clear goal of influencing results in 2012 in key states.
